ZH: 当我听到突然的爆炸声，我吓得激灵一下。
EN: I was startled when I heard a sudden explosion sound.

ZH: 经过悬崖边时，我不小心一激灵，差点失去平衡。
EN: When I passed by the edge of the cliff, I accidentally startled and almost lost my balance.

ZH: 黑暗的房间里突然亮起一束强光，让我激灵了一下。
EN: A beam of strong light suddenly lit up in the dark room, startling me.

ZH: 突然传来的警报声让大家激灵一下，纷纷朝着安全出口跑去。
EN: The sudden alarm sound startled everyone, and they all ran towards the emergency exit.

ZH: 我听到附近的树林里传来激灵的声音，以为是有人在靠近。
EN: I heard a rustling sound coming from the nearby woods and thought someone was approaching.

ZH: 他突然从后面摸了我一下，把我吓得激灵一下。
EN: He suddenly touched me from behind, startling me.

ZH: 小狗突然从草丛中冲出来，吓得我一个激灵。
EN: The puppy suddenly rushed out from the bushes, giving me a start.

ZH: 剧院里突然灯光一亮，观众不禁激灵了一下。
EN: The lights in the theater suddenly brightened, causing the audience to startle.

ZH: 我正在专心读书，突然被门铃声激灵了一下。
EN: I was concentrating on reading when suddenly the doorbell made me startle.

ZH: 她突然大喊一声，吓得我心里一激灵。
EN: She suddenly shouted, giving me a start.

ZH: 深夜里突然传来的枪声让人吓得激灵一下。
EN: The sudden sound of gunshots in the middle of the night startled people.

ZH: 我正走在马路上，突然听到汽车刹车声，吓得激灵了一下。
EN: I was walking on the street when suddenly I heard the sound of a car brakes, giving me a start.

ZH: 窗外传来的巨大轰鸣声把我吓得激灵一下。
EN: The loud roar coming from outside the window startled me.

ZH: 他不经意地拍了我一下，吓得我一个激灵。
EN: He casually slapped me, giving me a start.

ZH: 突然破晓的鞭炮声让我吓得激灵一下。
EN: The sudden sound of firecrackers at dawn startled me.

ZH: 窗外传来的雷声吓得我一个激灵。
EN: The thunderous sound from outside the window gave me a start.

ZH: 她蹑手蹑脚地走过来，突然摸了我的背一下，把我吓得激灵一下。
EN: She sneaked up to me and suddenly tapped my back, startling me.

ZH: 苍蝇突然从我面前飞过，吓得我一个激灵。
EN: A fly suddenly flew past me, giving me a start.

ZH: 我不小心碰到一个陷阱，吓得激灵了一下。
EN: I accidentally touched a trap, giving me a start.

ZH: 老鼠突然从角落里冲出来，吓得我一个激灵。
EN: A rat suddenly rushed out from the corner, startling me.
